      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DVtS8Y2DWO0/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/649548335_17943787092137198_1205972015014856796_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_s1080x1080_sh2.08_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=109&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzg0OTgxNjU3MTE1NDA5NzA3Ng%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjE0NDB4MTQ0MC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=wn6iGNQddEEQ7kNvwFY5D9r&amp;_nc_oc=Adr4tG1em1v2JYXm5Mfn8Zy2XRtwJhAe1SrDPHKuVNZvFrHR8cW-nVJsJEcP_Wl6ad8&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=teOxr9TEVeZ_QoQ_DOHk8g&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfzmEWKuiJaa3mR2rUZYa1Qh_nQu_taP4zSJS5X91Jb7ug&amp;oe=69CA1A46" alt="Instagram billede fra @trophysophie" /></p><p><strong>@trophysophie</strong></p><p>RONNIE’S BIG DEA<br/>
 <br/>
Written by<br/>
SOPHIE BECKER<br/>
 <br/>
Starring<br/>
SOPHIE BECKER<br/>
RONNIE WOODS<br/>
​<br/>
Directed by<br/>
JOS HOWARD DEMME<br/>
​<br/>
Wednesday. April 1, 8pm<br/>
Thursday, April 2, 8pm<br/>
Friday, April 3, 8pm<br/>
Saturday, April 4, 8pm<br/>
Sunday, April 5, 8pm<br/>
Tuesday, April 7, 8pm<br/>
Wednesday, April 8, 8pm<br/>
<br/>
$35 / $25 / $19* – Seating is limited.<br/>
TICKET LINK IN BIO.<br/>
*$19 tickets available for audiences ages 26 and under.<br/>
<br/>
-<br/>
<br/>
Did you think of that great idea first?  Act too slowly, and it may grow legs and walk off on its own. <br/>
<br/>
Sophie wants to be the greatest ventriloquist in the world. By her side is Ronnie – the matchstick with curves, the visionary, a cut above the rest. But when Ronnie branches out for a taste of independence, their bond begins to splinter.<br/>
 <br/>
–<br/>
​​<br/>
As a beauty influencer and interior designer, Ronnie Woods examines the intersection of objectification and embodied consciousness through a lens of dummy advocacy. She has appeared on NBC, Subway Takes with Kareem Rahma, and in The New York Times Style Section. Fresh from her European tour, Ronnie is now turning inward and penning her memoir, The Dummy in Me. Ronnie is excited to be making her New Theater Hollywood debut. <br/>
​<br/>
Sophie Becker is a New York-based performer and actor who the New York Times hailed as “The Downtown Ventriloquist”. Her work explores recursive identity and popular culture through a cast of recurring characters, including her dummy Ronnie. Sophie has performed at MoMA PS1 (NY), SculptureCenter (NY), C-mine (Belgium), De Studio (Belgium), Art Omi (Ghent, NY), and NADA Miami (Miami, FL), among others. She was a 2025 artist-in-residence at Kunstplaats Vonk and is included in the 2026 exhibition Greater New York at MoMA PS1.</p>]]></description>
