Sophie Becker is a New York-based performer and actor who the New York Times hailed as “The Downtown Ventriloquist”. Her work explores recursive identity and popular culture through a cast of recurring characters, including her dummy Ronnie. Sophie has performed at MoMA PS1 (NY), SculptureCenter (NY), C-mine (Belgium), De Studio (Belgium), Art Omi (Ghent, NY), and NADA Miami (Miami, FL), among others. She was a 2025 artist-in-residence at Kunstplaats Vonk and is included in the 2026 exhibition Greater New York at MoMA PS1.</p>]]></content:encoded>
